//  !NOTE
//  In the 'res_prop' macro there are 2 ways to calculate 'R' one is:
//  Calculation for resistor ( not metal ) R.
//  rcon = (cres*pitch)/w
//  R=2*rcon + rsh*l/(w-dw)
//  L- resistor Body length
//  W- Width
//  Rc' - contact resistance per width (= typical single contact resistance* contact pitch).
//  The same macro is applicable for metal resistors only R_contact should be set to 0.
//  This code is commeneted out and should be used explicitly by the user by uncommenting the code

